They are the brands that Britain grew up with but 53 of the top 100 are losing sales – many despite slashing prices.

Famous names like Silver Spoon sugar, Cadbury, Whiskas, Heinz and Kingsmill are suffering sales falls of more than 10per cent as shoppers switch to budget chains.

The nation’s fastest growing stores, Aldi and Lidl, effectively ban many of the top brands from their shelves.

